output_list.vulnerability: Integer Overflow, Bad Randomness, Access Control, Typos Constructor, Token Devalue
output_list.criticism: The `distributeToken` function does not contain any checks to prevent multiple vulnerabilities such as integer overflow, bad randomness, access control, typos in the constructor, and token devalue. This can lead to unauthorized increases in the `balances[msg.sender]` of the sender, which can result in loss of funds.
